by Wexas » Tue Dec 22, 2020 5:17 pm

Despite Synne referring to both the corporation and the country, the two are legally not the same. Indeed, both are separate but have a symbiotic relationship allowing for the state of Synne to have low taxes while, presumably, the corporation of Synne has a lot of freedom. Of course, both are under the (either De Jure or De Facto) autocratic rule of the CEO of Synne Industries, which acts as both Head of Corporation and Head of State. Also, there is a direct democratic system of government, though members of parliament have 5 votes while citizens only have one.

This is a rather bright view of a corporate pseudo-cyberpunk (before it was cool) nation. At least, until you dig too deep and find something you don't wanna see... RSI strikes fear into the hearts of even the most powerful of FFT Powerwankers.
